Metadata: Careers in Science (Wildlife Biologist): Cheryle Strong (Webinar November 4, 2020)
Growing Engineers and Marine Scientists Webinar November 4, 2020, Corvallis, Oregon
Oregon Sea Grant and published on YouTube December 14, 2020

This career webinar is for students grades 6-12 who want to explore careers in marine science. It features Cheryl Strong, a wildlife biologist with the U.S. Fish and Wildlife Service in Newport, Oregon. She helps manage the western snowy plover, which nests on the beach.
